    "en": {
      "title": "44 prisoners who escaped from Kandakadu are still missing",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Welikanda Police requests the public to inform the Welikanda Police Station Commander that 44 inmates who escaped from the Kandakadu Treatment and Rehabilitation Center are still missing and if they have any information about them.",
        "With the unrest in the Kandakadu Rehabilitation Center on the 29th, more than 700 inmates escaped, of which 679 people have been arrested and brought to court, the police said. Another 272 inmates are staying at the rehabilitation center.",
        "The police further request the public to inform the Welikanda Police Station Commander at 0718591235 or Welikanda Police at 027 2259143 if they have any information about the 44 missing persons.",
        "Mr. Samantha Rathnayake said that more operations will be carried out to find the missing inmates and that these missing persons may be hiding in their homes or relative's homes and that they should not be hidden and handed over to the police immediately."
      ],
